article_title: Smoother Launch for Health-Law Website, Administration Officials Say
article_text:
WASHINGTON—About 100,000 people submitted applications for health insurance on the first day of the relaunch of Healthcare.gov, the online insurance marketplace at the heart of the president’s health-care law, Sylvia Mathews Burwell, the secretary of the Department of Health and Human Services, said on Sunday.
